
[1]excoriate

   EXCO'RIATE, v.t. [Low L. excorio; ex and corium, skin, hide.]

   To flay; to strip or wear off the skin; to abrade; to gall; to break
   and remove the cuticle in any manner, as by rubbing, beating, or by the
   action of acrid substances.
